<h1>Shipping Policy</h1>
<p class="legal-page__meta"><em>Last updated: April 9, 2026</em></p>
<h2>Where We Ship</h2>
<p><strong>United States only.</strong> We do not currently offer international shipping.</p>
<h2>Carriers</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>UPS Ground</strong> — primary carrier for apparel</li>
<li><strong>FedEx, USPS, LaserShip</strong> — used for promo products and other non-apparel categories</li>
</ul>
<p>Carrier selection depends on the product category, destination, and speed required for your order.</p>
<h2>Production Lead Time</h2>
<p><strong>12 business days</strong> from pre-production proof approval for custom apparel, unless rush production is purchased. Promo products and other product categories vary — we'll give you a firm date at quote time.</p>
<p>The clock starts <strong>when you approve the proof</strong>, not when you place the order. Fast proof turnaround = faster ship date.</p>
<h2>Rush Production</h2>
<p>Rush production is available for time-sensitive orders. Pricing is per order based on quantity, product type, and turnaround. <strong>Rush must be confirmed in writing before it can be billed.</strong></p>
<h2>Rush Shipping</h2>
<p>Expedited shipping (UPS 2-Day, Next-Day Air, FedEx Express, etc.) is available at the carrier's published rate with <strong>no markup from us</strong>.</p>
<h2>Ship Dates vs. In-Hands Dates</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ship dates are committed.</strong> When we say we'll ship on a date, we ship on that date.</li>
<li><strong>In-hands dates are estimates.</strong> Carrier transit times are out of our control, so in-hands dates are our best projection based on the carrier's published service.</li>
</ul>
<p>We will keep you in the loop on any delays on our side.</p>
<h2>Lost or Damaged in Transit</h2>
<p>Loss and damage in transit are the carrier's responsibility, not ours. If your shipment is lost or arrives damaged:</p>
<ol>
<li>Report it to us within 5 business days of delivery (or the expected delivery date for a lost shipment)</li>
<li>We'll help you file and track a carrier claim</li>
<li>We'll help reconcile the situation where we can</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>If a carrier delay impacts a time-sensitive event, we will refund the shipping charge in good faith</strong> — even though the delay itself isn't our fault.</p>
<h2>Shipping Costs</h2>
<p>Shipping is billed at cost on most orders. We will always confirm shipping charges with you before they're locked in.</p>
<h2>Questions</h2>
<p>For questions about a specific shipment, carrier claim, or shipping method:</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> solepdistributions@gmail.com <strong>Phone:</strong> (978) 844-6206</p>
